name: Proxima Centauri b
description:
Proxima Centauri b is the closest exo planet to our home solar system. Approximately 4.24 light years away scientists are hopeful that the possibility of life on this planet is high. It rests in the Southern Constellation of Centaurus and could possibly be the first exoplanet for humans to visit in the future.
